data.value: This study aims to assist local cacao growers and chocolatiers alike by providing them with a non-biased computer system that would identify and classify the fermentation level of the cacao beans to be sold and bought, respectively. This would make deals between both parties fair and non-biased so as to give both parties what they deserve – local cacao growers will be paid according to the quality of the beans they produced and processed, while local chocolatiers would get their money’s worth with the cacao beans they bought.
